<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>Shila and Bobby start cycling toward each other from two towns <m>{50}</m> km apart. Bobby cycles <m>{\frac{17}{2}}</m> km/h faster than Shila. If they meet after <m>{3}</m> hours:</p>
<p>Find their speeds.</p>
<p>Bobby's speed: <fillin characters="6" name="ans1"/>  km/h  </p>
<p>Shila's speed: <fillin characters="6" name="ans2"/> km/h  </p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>Let Shila's speed = <m>v</m> km/h.</p>
<p>Then Bobby's speed = <m>v + {\frac{17}{2}}</m> km/h.</p>

<p>When cycling toward each other, their relative speed is the sum:</p>
<p><m>v + (v + {\frac{17}{2}}) = 2v + {\frac{17}{2}}</m> km/h</p>

<p>They cover <m>{50}</m> km in <m>{3}</m> hour, so:</p>
<p><m>(2v + {\frac{17}{2}}) \times {3} = {50}</m></p>
<p><m>2v + {\frac{17}{2}} = \frac{ {50} }{ {3} }</m></p>
<p><m>2v = {\frac{50}{3}} - {\frac{17}{2}}</m></p>
<p><m>v = \frac{ {\frac{50}{3}} - {\frac{17}{2}} }{2} = {5} \text{ km/h}</m></p>

<p>Bobby's speed = <m>v + {\frac{17}{2}} = {5} + {\frac{17}{2}} = {\frac{27}{2}} \text{ km/h}</m></p>

<p>Therefore, their speeds are:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Bobby: <m>{\frac{27}{2}}</m> km/h</li>
  <li>Shila: <m>{5}</m> km/h</li>
</ul></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>\frac{27}{2}</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>5</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>